init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But, I suppose we should do something about them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The President of the United States was sitting in his office, reading a book.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Mr. President, we have a call for you from the Prime Minister of England."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, that was a real kick in the teeth."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The next day, the President addressed the nation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Fellow Americans, I have some news that may be hard to hear.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He paused for a moment, "We are not alone in the world.
